    "causal_summary": "`contenthash` is a raw sha256 with no normalization (`memory-parser.ts:914`; deep-dive-report Chain A step 1 cites :913), so any CRLF/trailing-whitespace or `memory.continuity.lastupdatedat` churn registers as new content; each same-path re-save then retires the predecessor to `tier='deprecated'` and inserts a new row, accumulating snapshots unboundedly (Chain A steps 2-3)",
